\begin_layout Standard
To bring the whole MPO into left canonical form we simply start at site
 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 and sweep to the right, resulting in the following sequence
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\hat{H}=\boldsymbol{ğ‘™}\hat{W}^{1}\hat{W}^{2}\hat{W}^{3}\cdots\hat{W}^{N-1}\hat{W}^{N}\boldsymbol{ğ‘Ÿ}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\hat{QR}\left(\boldsymbol{ğ‘™}\hat{W}^{1}\right)\hat{W}^{2}\hat{W}^{3}\cdots\hat{W}^{N-1}\hat{W}^{N}\boldsymbol{ğ‘Ÿ}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\hat{Q}_{+}^{1}R_{+}^{1}\hat{W}^{2}\hat{W}^{3}\cdots\hat{W}^{N-1}\hat{W}^{N}\boldsymbol{ğ‘Ÿ}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\hat{W}_{L}^{1}R_{+}^{1}\hat{W}^{2}\hat{W}^{3}\cdots\hat{W}^{L-1}\hat{W}^{L}\boldsymbol{ğ‘Ÿ}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\hat{W}_{L}^{1}\left(R_{+}^{1}\hat{W}^{2}\right)\hat{W}^{3}\cdots\hat{W}^{N-1}\hat{W}^{N}\boldsymbol{ğ‘Ÿ}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\hat{W}_{L}^{1}\hat{W}^{2\prime}\hat{W}^{3}\cdots\hat{W}^{N-1}\hat{W}^{N}\boldsymbol{ğ‘Ÿ}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\hat{W}_{L}^{1}\hat{QR}\left(\hat{W}^{2\prime}\right)\hat{W}^{3}\cdots\hat{W}^{N-1}\hat{W}^{N}\boldsymbol{ğ‘Ÿ}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\vdots
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\hat{W}_{L}^{1}\hat{W}_{L}^{2}\hat{W}_{L}^{3}\cdots\hat{W}_{L}^{N-1}\hat{W}_{L}^{N}
\]

\end_inset

Of course we just sweep backwards using 
\begin_inset Formula $RQ$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $LQ$
\end_inset

 decomposition to get a right canonical form.
